To sum this all up, always be on alert while interacting with anyone in the space. 

NEVER GIVE OUT YOUR SEEDPHRASE

There is nothing worse than having your hard earned $$ stolen by someone pretending to help you. 

10/10

Once they secure the bag, their followers are left holding a worthless JPEG. 

Always do your own research and never enter solely based on the fact that someone else bought it. If you do, 9 out of 10 times you‚Äôll get REKT.

9/10

There are countless examples of influencers using their followers as ‚Äúexit liquidity‚Äù. 

They tweet about a project, their followers buy into it; making the price sky rocket. Then they dump the project for a crazy %‚Äôs of returns. 

8/10

Let‚Äôs move onto twitter #crypto influencers. 

Just because someone has a massive following does not mean they are trustworthy people. The top influencers stay anonymous. 

IF YOU SEE AN INFLUENCER POST ABOUT A PROJECT, ASSUME THEY ARE USING THEIR FOLLOWERS TO PUMP IT.

7/10

The average person in nfts doesn‚Äôt understand at a deep level how the blockchain works. 

Once we are at a global level, the amount of scams and thefts will rise.
It happens all the time with the @BoredApeYC. Quarter million dollar assets stolen in minutes. 

6/10

There are brilliant developers in the #web3 space that prey on people that don‚Äôt know better. If you click a link that is sent to you, they can deploy a smart contract that transfers all of your wallet holdings to their wallet. This happens all the time. 

5/10

There are friendly people in discords that will help you. There are also experienced individuals that will take advantage and try to scam and steal your assets.
